cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new learning algorithm for deep networks used to approximate traditional image operators with parameters. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed algorithm involves learning from the operator parameters to dynamically adjust the weights of a deep network, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of a weight learning network and end-to-end joint training further supports the possibility of belonging to these sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed framework involves dynamically changing the weights of only one single layer of the base network while sharing most computation cost, which suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments and results related to image processing, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
